               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the scribe; a few groups of lines (alternating with black lines) in the incipit page; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The Vita of Kiros is preceded by a short theological treatise on the Trinity (fol. 5rab).</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="coloph1">
                     <colophon>
                        <locus target="45ra"/>Fol. 45rab: ተፈጸመ፡ ገድለ፡ ኪሮስ፡ በሰላመ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አብ፡ አሜን፡ በ፲ወ፱፻፴ወ፮፡ ዓመተ፡ ምህረት፡ በዘበነ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ወንጌላዊ፡ ሌሊቱ፡ ፪ መዓልቱ፡ ፳ወ፭፡ ዘጸሐፋኂ፡ አባ፡ ክንፈ፡ ገብርኤል፡ ፍስሐ።<foreign xml:lang="en">Fol. 45rab: The Vita of Kiros has been completed in the peace of God the Father, amen. In the year of mercy 1936 in the era of John the Evangelist, night 2, day 25. ʾAbba Kǝnfä Gäbrǝʾel Fǝssǝḥa is the one who wrote it. </foreign>
                        <note>The colophon states that the Ms. was completed in 1936 year of mercy (= 1943/44 A.D.) and that the scribe was ʾabba Kǝnfä Gäbrǝʾel Fǝśśǝḥa.</note>
                     </colophon>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
